<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Davy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Davy,</orth> name; 1) <emph>St. D.'s day</emph> (26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Aug.), the day of the battle of Crecy, in whose memory the Welsh wore leek in their caps: <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.108" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 2</bibl>. -- 2) a servant of Justice Shallow: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 2</bibl> 10 etc. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 10</bibl> -- 3) <emph>D. Gam,</emph> slain at Agincourt: <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 109</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>